Marry me. Give me thine hand.

246
00:12:31,250 --> 00:12:34,750
I'm afraid you'll
have to count meow-t.

247
00:12:34,833 --> 00:12:37,583
I swear, I am in love with you!

248
00:12:37,666 --> 00:12:39,041
[NEKOHIME sighs]

249
00:12:39,125 --> 00:12:42,416
[NEKOHIME] Sorry, but I'm
actually a guy in real life.

250
00:12:43,333 --> 00:12:44,791
I'm a middle-aged dude.

251
00:12:44,875 --> 00:12:46,791
At first I wanted to
ogle a sexy avatar,

252
00:12:46,875 --> 00:12:48,458
but then I got caught up
in cross-playing.

253
00:12:48,541 --> 00:12:49,916
[RUSIAN]
Huh?

254
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:52,166
I mean, what chick would say
"meow" puns in real life?

255
00:12:52,250 --> 00:12:54,583
Not the kinda girl
you'd wanna date.

256
00:12:56,833 --> 00:13:00,375
[RUSIAN, HIDEKI scream]

257
00:13:00,458 --> 00:13:01,958
[HIDEKI]
Damn it! Damn it!

258
00:13:02,041 --> 00:13:03,791
I swear, I will never
trust another girl

259
00:13:03,875 --> 00:13:05,375
I meet on the net again!

260
00:13:05,458 --> 00:13:08,500
For as long as I live!

261
00:13:09,541 --> 00:13:11,958
[APRICOT, SCHWEIN laughing]

262
00:13:12,041 --> 00:13:13,583
[RUSIAN] You guys don't
have to laugh that hard!

263
00:13:13,666 --> 00:13:15,875
[SCHWEIN] That chapter of
your life is beyond dark.

264
00:13:15,958 --> 00:13:18,833
Ah, the majesty of young love.

265
00:13:18,916 --> 00:13:20,125
Fart-knockers.

266
00:13:20,208 --> 00:13:21,583
[RUSIAN]
The thing is, Nekohime,

267
00:13:21,666 --> 00:13:24,500
the girl I first declared my
love to, was super cute,

268
00:13:24,583 --> 00:13:25,875
had good taste
in equipment,

269
00:13:25,958 --> 00:13:28,625
was nice to everyone she
played with and played well.

270
00:13:28,708 --> 00:13:31,958
She was the ideal girl--
I mean, girl character.

271
00:13:32,041 --> 00:13:34,708
The sheer shock of her
revelation was devastating.

272
00:13:34,791 --> 00:13:36,750
To the point that I left
the guild I was with,

273
00:13:36,833 --> 00:13:38,333
and for nearly a year after,

274
00:13:38,416 --> 00:13:42,125
I stuck with solo
play exclusively.

275
00:13:42,208 --> 00:13:47,500
Then, in my solitude,
I arrived at a certain truth.

276
00:13:47,583 --> 00:13:49,375
Who cares as long
as they're cute!

277
00:13:49,458 --> 00:13:51,541
Even if they are dudes in
real life, I don't care!

278
00:13:51,625 --> 00:13:53,166
As long as they're cute in game.

279
00:13:53,250 --> 00:13:55,041
Ultimately, it was the
cuteness in the game

280
00:13:55,125 --> 00:13:56,833
I was enamored with.

281
00:13:56,916 --> 00:14:00,166
Yes, I discovered the horrible
truth lurking on the web.

282
00:14:00,250 --> 00:14:03,083
Rusian, are you mad at me?

283
00:14:03,166 --> 00:14:04,458
For telling everyone
what happened

284
00:14:04,541 --> 00:14:05,875
with you and the cat girl?

285
00:14:05,958 --> 00:14:09,041
That kinda stuff happens
all the time, so don't worry.

286
00:14:09,125 --> 00:14:11,833
Thank you so much, Rusian!

287
00:14:11,916 --> 00:14:13,000
I love you.

288
00:14:13,083 --> 00:14:14,583
[gasps]

289
00:14:14,666 --> 00:14:17,833
Huh. Just calm down.
You gotta cool it, Hideki.

290
00:14:17,916 --> 00:14:20,166
You know from experience that
if you take it too seriously,

291
00:14:20,250 --> 00:14:21,083
you'll only regret it.

292
00:14:21,166 --> 00:14:22,458
[APRICOT]
It makes sense.

293
00:14:22,541 --> 00:14:24,916
Now I see why you were
so hesitant to agree.

294
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:26,916
All this spouse stuff has
nothing to do with me

295
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:28,125
in real life,

296
00:14:28,208 --> 00:14:29,833
but in the world of
the game, Ako is Ako.

297
00:14:29,916 --> 00:14:32,541
Just so you know,
I actually am female.

298
00:14:32,625 --> 00:14:35,166
Yeah, fine. If you
say so, then you are.

299
00:14:35,250 --> 00:14:36,375
At least to you, that is.

300
00:14:36,458 --> 00:14:37,875
No, no.

301
00:14:37,958 --> 00:14:40,125
In real life, I'm a nerdy,
nose-in-her-book kind of girl.

302
00:14:40,208 --> 00:14:41,708
[SCHWEIN]
Whoa, hold on.

303
00:14:41,791 --> 00:14:44,500
You shouldn't admit something
like that in open chat, Ako.

304
00:14:44,583 --> 00:14:46,541
It's the greatest
net taboo of all.

305
00:14:46,625 --> 00:14:48,416
I had no idea.

306
00:14:48,500 --> 00:14:50,291
Taboos are ludicrous.

307
00:14:50,375 --> 00:14:53,375
I, for example, am a high
school girl in real life.

308
00:14:53,458 --> 00:14:55,625
You, Master?
A high school girl?

309
00:14:55,708 --> 00:14:57,833
With that premium gear?
Not a chance.

310
00:14:57,916 --> 00:14:58,708
Impossible.

311
00:14:58,791 --> 00:15:00,166
Seriously, no way.

312
00:15:00,250 --> 00:15:01,750
I'm pouring my heart
out to my friends,

313
00:15:01,833 --> 00:15:03,791
and this is how you treat me?

314
00:15:03,875 --> 00:15:06,500
Actually admitting it
feels kind of nice,

315
00:15:06,583 --> 00:15:09,000
but what if we did this?

316
00:15:12,791 --> 00:15:14,375
"Guild Alley Cats..."

317
00:15:14,458 --> 00:15:16,458
"...First Offline Get Together"?

318
00:15:16,541 --> 00:15:19,000
To be held in real life?

319
00:15:19,083 --> 00:15:21,875
[RUSIAN, AKO, SCHWEIN]
Wha--?!

320
00:15:30,250 --> 00:15:32,541
Guess they aren't here yet.

321
00:15:32,625 --> 00:15:34,750
And what are the odds that
we're all pretty local?

322
00:15:34,833 --> 00:15:37,666
We've been a guild for almost
a year now, and never knew?

323
00:15:37,750 --> 00:15:40,916
"I'm by the big tree
in front of the station.

324
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:43,708
In a white T-shirt."

325
00:15:45,208 --> 00:15:48,291
[GIRL]
Excuse me? Rusian?

326
00:15:48,375 --> 00:15:51,333
[HIDEKI] Um, yeah.
That's me. I'm Rusian.

327
00:15:51,416 --> 00:15:55,375
[GIRL] I-I knew it was you,
and I'm A-Ako.

328
00:15:55,458 --> 00:15:57,208
From the game?

329
00:16:07,750 --> 00:16:10,791
Hi, nice to meet you.

330
00:16:11,875 --> 00:16:16,375
[HIDEKI]
Wow, Ako? The real Ako.

331
00:16:16,458 --> 00:16:17,916
[AKO]
Yes.

332
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:21,125
You're a girl... in real life.
You aren't just pretending.

333
00:16:21,208 --> 00:16:25,541
Um... Rusian? Ah!

334
00:16:25,625 --> 00:16:27,916
Wow! Rusian! It's really you!

335
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:30,208
My husband Rusian,
live in the flesh!

336
00:16:30,291 --> 00:16:32,125
Cool it! Stop calling
me by my username!

337
00:16:32,208 --> 00:16:33,666
What if someone I know sees us?

338
00:16:33,750 --> 00:16:37,125
[AKANE]
You're Rusian?

339
00:16:37,208 --> 00:16:39,083
Nishimura? You're him?

340
00:16:39,166 --> 00:16:41,625
[HIDEKI]
Wait, Segawa? Huh... Umm...

341
00:16:41,708 --> 00:16:43,000
You already know each other?

342
00:16:43,083 --> 00:16:47,125
Um, kinda. I mean,
I've seen him before.

343
00:16:47,208 --> 00:16:49,916
Well, I'm glad to see
everyone got here safely.

344
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:51,375
It's you.

345
00:16:51,458 --> 00:16:53,291
Madam President?

346
00:16:53,375 --> 00:16:54,625
[KYOH]
Not today.

347
00:16:54,708 --> 00:16:57,083
I'm not here as the student
council president,

348
00:16:57,166 --> 00:17:00,458
but as the Alley Cats'
Guildmaster, the wizard Apricot!

349
00:17:00,541 --> 00:17:02,333
[HIDEKI, AKANE gasp]

350
00:17:02,416 --> 00:17:03,625
[KYOH]
You must be Rusian,

351
00:17:03,708 --> 00:17:05,833
and the one clinging to you,
I assume, is Ako.

352
00:17:05,916 --> 00:17:09,958
Yeah, that's right.
Wait, you said everyone.

353
00:17:10,041 --> 00:17:11,000
[AKANE gasps]

354
00:17:12,541 --> 00:17:14,333
[HIDEKI]
You? You're Schwein?

355
00:17:14,416 --> 00:17:16,583
Oh. Hi, Schew.
It's a pleasure to meet you.

356
00:17:16,666 --> 00:17:18,708
Ah! No! Don't call
me that in public!

357
00:17:18,791 --> 00:17:19,875
No way.

358
00:17:19,958 --> 00:17:21,291
That's exactly what
I was going to say!

359
00:17:21,375 --> 00:17:22,791
[chuckles]

360
00:17:22,875 --> 00:17:24,333
All right,

361
00:17:24,416 --> 00:17:27,666
it's time for Guild Alley Cats'
First Offline Get-Together!

362
00:17:27,750 --> 00:17:29,250
Let's have fun!

363
00:17:29,333 --> 00:17:30,583
[AKO squeals]

364
00:17:30,666 --> 00:17:33,958
[AKO] Rusian, it's you!
I can barely believe it!

365
00:17:34,041 --> 00:17:35,333
You're warm and everything!

366
00:17:35,416 --> 00:17:36,916
You're makin' it sound
like I'm a mannequin

367
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:38,416
that came to life or somethin'.

368
00:17:38,500 --> 00:17:42,125
Rusian. Rusian.
Mighty, noble Rusian.

369
00:17:42,208 --> 00:17:43,958
Please cut it out.

370
00:17:45,500 --> 00:17:47,416
He's Rusian, all right.

371
00:17:47,500 --> 00:17:48,666
How can you
still be that happy

372
00:17:48,750 --> 00:17:51,083
after he just treated
you so rudely?

373
00:17:51,166 --> 00:17:55,000
Now then, let's start off
with proper introductions.

374
00:17:55,083 --> 00:17:57,250
My name is Kyoh Goshoeen.

375
00:17:57,333 --> 00:17:59,041
I'm a second year
at Maegasaki High

376
00:17:59,125 --> 00:18:00,958
and the student
council president.

377
00:18:01,041 --> 00:18:02,583
I came by on my way
home from school,

378
00:18:02,666 --> 00:18:05,291
so excuse me for not
dressing to the occasion.

379
00:18:05,375 --> 00:18:06,833
We're already good friends,

380
00:18:06,916 --> 00:18:09,041
but we're also meeting
for the first time.

381
00:18:09,125 --> 00:18:11,833
Thus, as questing has forged
our bonds of friendship.

382
00:18:11,916 --> 00:18:15,041
May socializing take it
to the next level!

383
00:18:18,625 --> 00:18:19,958
Now It's your turn.

384
00:18:20,041 --> 00:18:22,458
[AKANE]
Wait, me?

385
00:18:22,541 --> 00:18:24,416
I'm Akane Segawa.

386
00:18:24,500 --> 00:18:27,541
I'm a first year at
Maegasaki and--

387
00:18:27,625 --> 00:18:29,750
And well... here I am.

388
00:18:29,833 --> 00:18:31,166
[KYOH]
I understand, Schwein.

389
00:18:31,250 --> 00:18:33,375
It must be embarrassing
to go by a name like that

390
00:18:33,458 --> 00:18:35,958
in such a public place.

391
00:18:36,041 --> 00:18:37,208
Your name, "Schwein,"

392
00:18:37,291 --> 00:18:39,916
is actually the German
word for "pig."

393
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:42,000
I doubt there are many
young ladies out there

394
00:18:42,083 --> 00:18:44,291
who would wanna say,
"Hello, my name is Pig.

395
00:18:44,375 --> 00:18:46,875
It's a pleasure to meet you."

396
00:18:46,958 --> 00:18:48,958
[AKANE]
No way...

397
00:18:49,041 --> 00:18:53,208
A pig? Schwein?

398
00:18:53,291 --> 00:18:55,500
I take it you've been using
the name without knowing.

399
00:18:55,583 --> 00:18:56,958
[AKANE whines]

400
00:18:57,041 --> 00:18:58,916
Of course I didn't know!

401
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:01,500
Who in their right mind would
ever choose "Pig" for a name?

402
00:19:01,583 --> 00:19:03,625
I just picked "Schwein"
because it sounded cool!

403
00:19:03,708 --> 00:19:05,666
[AKO]
Poor, Schew.

404
00:19:05,750 --> 00:19:07,583
My sympathies.

405
00:19:07,666 --> 00:19:08,916
We've been playing
together forever,

406
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:10,500
how come you never
said anything?

407
00:19:10,583 --> 00:19:13,791
I thought you chose a
joke name on purpose.

408
00:19:16,541 --> 00:19:17,416
[AKANE]
That's right.

409
00:19:17,500 --> 00:19:19,291
I'm the one you call Schwein.

410
00:19:19,375 --> 00:19:21,750
And anyone who starts
calling me pig...

411
00:19:21,833 --> 00:19:24,250
...gets stuck like a pig.

412
00:19:24,333 --> 00:19:25,916
That's all.

413
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:27,666
All right, then. Rusian?

414
00:19:27,750 --> 00:19:28,916
[HIDEKI]
Okay.

415
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:33,000
So. Hi there. I'm... I'm Rusian.

416
00:19:33,083 --> 00:19:35,000
It's totally embarrassing
to introduce myself

417
00:19:35,083 --> 00:19:35,958
as my character!

418
00:19:36,041 --> 00:19:37,083
Don't worry, Nishimura,

419
00:19:37,166 --> 00:19:38,833
your existence is
an embarrassment.

420
00:19:38,916 --> 00:19:40,791
[HIDEKI]
That's mean!

421
00:19:40,875 --> 00:19:42,333
Where was I?

422
00:19:42,416 --> 00:19:44,250
My name's Hideki Nishimura.

423
00:19:44,333 --> 00:19:46,083
I'm also a first
year at Maegasaki,

424
00:19:46,166 --> 00:19:47,500
but I'm not in any clubs.

425
00:19:47,583 --> 00:19:51,125
No special talents. My hobbies
are, uh, online gaming.

426
00:19:51,208 --> 00:19:52,583
And that's it.

427
00:19:54,291 --> 00:19:57,000
[AKO]
Hi. My name is Ako.

428
00:19:57,083 --> 00:20:00,000
I always end up as a burden
on you in <i>Legendary Age</i> .

429
00:20:00,083 --> 00:20:01,375
I'm sorry.

430
00:20:01,458 --> 00:20:03,333
Oh, and I'm also a
first year student

431
00:20:03,416 --> 00:20:05,708
at the same high school
as the rest of you.

432
00:20:05,791 --> 00:20:07,041
So then we're classmates?

433
00:20:07,125 --> 00:20:10,250
That's right, I was pleasantly
surprised as well.

434
00:20:10,333 --> 00:20:12,416
My full name is Ako Tamaki,

435
00:20:12,500 --> 00:20:14,958
so you can just keep calling me
"Ako" like you always have.

436
00:20:15,041 --> 00:20:16,625
They're the same?

437
00:20:16,708 --> 00:20:19,125
[AKO]
Yes. Why? Is that unusual?

438
00:20:19,208 --> 00:20:21,541
Well, it's kind of
a net safety issue.

439
00:20:21,625 --> 00:20:22,458
Don't worry about it.

440
00:20:22,541 --> 00:20:24,166
[KYOH chuckles]

441
00:20:24,250 --> 00:20:26,166
How totally Ako.

442
00:20:27,625 --> 00:20:30,333
[AKO]
I'm not involved in any clubs.

443
00:20:30,416 --> 00:20:32,583
And I don't really
have friends at school.

444
00:20:32,666 --> 00:20:34,166
[BOTH gasp]

445
00:20:34,250 --> 00:20:36,166
I tend to sit alone,

446
00:20:36,250 --> 00:20:39,416
which gets the attention
of the other students.

447
00:20:40,458 --> 00:20:42,083
It-It's all right, Ako.

448
00:20:42,166 --> 00:20:43,375
I'm student council president,

449
00:20:43,458 --> 00:20:44,750
and I don't have
any friends either.

450
00:20:44,833 --> 00:20:47,041
Hey, think about this:
The four of us are friends!

451
00:20:47,125 --> 00:20:48,791
Yeah, he's right!

452
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:52,500
I really appreciate it,
you guys.

453
00:20:52,583 --> 00:20:55,125
I'm so happy to have
friends that I can talk to.

454
00:20:55,208 --> 00:20:57,750
Friends that I can
have fun with.

455
00:20:57,833 --> 00:21:00,458
I can't wait to see how
far our guild can go!

456
00:21:00,541 --> 00:21:03,833
[clapping]

457
00:21:09,500 --> 00:21:12,625
[HIDEKI]
Oh, yeah. Segawa?

458
00:21:12,708 --> 00:21:14,041
What now?

459
00:21:14,125 --> 00:21:15,625
When we were chatting in
the guild hall the other day,

460
00:21:15,708 --> 00:21:17,625
you were telling us that some
guy declared his love for you

461
00:21:17,708 --> 00:21:18,833
in real life, right?

462
00:21:18,916 --> 00:21:20,916
Yeah, that's right.
So what about it?

463
00:21:21,000 --> 00:21:23,125
[HIDEKI] Ha. I just
think it's kinda funny.

464
00:21:23,208 --> 00:21:25,458
Little Miss Popularity.

465
00:21:25,541 --> 00:21:27,083
Not really.

466
00:21:27,166 --> 00:21:29,250
[AKO]
Schew is a total normie.

467
00:21:29,333 --> 00:21:31,083
Schew is a total normie...

468
00:21:31,166 --> 00:21:32,375
Hey! Ako?

469
00:21:32,458 --> 00:21:33,625
Interesting.

470
00:21:33,708 --> 00:21:35,166
Let the record show
that Schwein,

471
00:21:35,250 --> 00:21:38,041
unlike the rest of us,
is a verified normie.

472
00:21:38,125 --> 00:21:41,125
You should pick us up
in your minivan next time.

473
00:21:43,875 --> 00:21:45,583
[HIDEKI]
Master, you too?

474
00:21:45,666 --> 00:21:47,916
[AKANE] Like I already said,
I told the guy no.

475
00:21:48,000 --> 00:21:50,541
I'm not interested in
going out with anyone.

476
00:21:50,625 --> 00:21:52,333
I've been told that
Maeda from Class 3

477
00:21:52,416 --> 00:21:54,583
is pretty popular
with the ladies.

478
00:21:54,666 --> 00:21:55,833
Is he just not your type?

479
00:21:55,916 --> 00:21:58,291
[AKANE]
I-It's not that.

480
00:21:58,375 --> 00:21:59,583
If I had a dumb boyfriend,

481
00:21:59,666 --> 00:22:01,291
it would cut into my time
playing video games.

482
00:22:01,375 --> 00:22:02,833
[HIDEKI]
That's why you turned him down?

483
00:22:02,916 --> 00:22:05,208
You wouldn't seriously want
something like that, would you?

484
00:22:05,291 --> 00:22:06,500
Definitely not for me.

485
00:22:06,583 --> 00:22:07,708
I'd turn him down.

486
00:22:07,791 --> 00:22:09,833
You genuinely would
rather play video games?

487
00:22:09,916 --> 00:22:11,791
[AKANE] Damn straight.
You got a problem with that?

488
00:22:11,875 --> 00:22:13,125
Nope.

489
00:22:13,208 --> 00:22:15,041
I definitely prefer this
to who you are at school.

490
00:22:15,125 --> 00:22:17,791
I don't think I should take
that statement as a compliment.

491
00:22:17,875 --> 00:22:20,041
[AKO] I may have an idea
to turn that around!

492
00:22:20,125 --> 00:22:22,166
So, Schew, have you ever
considered getting married

493
00:22:22,250 --> 00:22:23,708
in the game?

494
00:22:23,791 --> 00:22:26,083
Rusian and I did, and we've
been having fun ever since!

495
00:22:26,166 --> 00:22:28,166
You wouldn't lose any
gaming time that way.

496
00:22:28,250 --> 00:22:30,125
Plus, you'd be spending time
with the one you love.

497
00:22:30,208 --> 00:22:31,416
It's a total twofer!

498
00:22:31,500 --> 00:22:33,791
I think I'll pass, thanks.
It sounds gross.

499
00:22:33,875 --> 00:22:35,416
[HIDEKI]
That's mean!

500
00:22:35,500 --> 00:22:37,041
I think it's a great idea!

501
00:22:37,125 --> 00:22:38,833
Right, Rusian?

502
00:22:40,291 --> 00:22:42,916
Yeah, but I can still
hardly believe it myself.

503
00:22:43,000 --> 00:22:44,250
[AKO]
Huh?

504
00:22:44,333 --> 00:22:47,250
[HIDEKI]
Ako, you're so...

505
00:22:55,666 --> 00:22:58,291
I have a living, breathing
girl as my 2D wife.

506
00:22:58,375 --> 00:23:00,708
Oh, Rusian!

507
00:24:31,583 --> 00:24:33,333
[AKO] Are you trying
to humiliate me?

508
00:24:33,416 --> 00:24:34,958
Lately, it's been frowned
on for the heroine

509
00:24:35,041 --> 00:24:36,500
to be too forward
in Episode One,

510
00:24:36,583 --> 00:24:38,625
but you're taking it too far
the other way, Rusian!

511
00:24:38,708 --> 00:24:40,500
[HIDEKI]
I'm not the heroine here!

